<p>REQUEST</p>
<p>rogare refers to a request as a quiet utterance of a wish, and this request is directed to a person of similar status to the speaker.</p>
<p>orare refers to a quiet utterance of a wish directed at a superior.</p>
<p>obsecrare refers to an urgent and passionate request.</p>
<p>obtestari refers to an urgent and passionate request to a superior in a suppliant manner.</p>
<p>precari refers to a request to heaven, typically with raised hands.</p>
<p>supplicare refers to a passionate act of supplication in which one throws oneself on one's knees, or on the ground, and tyically wrings one's hands, but by extension the word also refers to any exceedingly polite and humble request, especially in polite discourse.</p>
